  <H2>Phase Transition Diagram</H2>

  <Body>The behavior of the Kuramoto model can be summarized in a bifurcation diagram showing r versus K:</Body>

  <Code lang="plaintext">
     r
     |
   1 |                    ________________
     |                  /
     |                 /
     |                /
     |              /
   0 |_____________/________________________ K
     0            K_c

  Incoherent (r=0)  |  Synchronized (r>0)
  </Code>

  <Body>The diagram shows:</Body>
  <Body>• For K &lt; K_c: Only the incoherent state r = 0 is stable</Body>
  <Body>• At K = K_c: A continuous bifurcation occurs</Body>
  <Body>• For K &gt; K_c: A stable synchronized branch emerges with r increasing toward 1</Body>

  <Body>This phase transition is analogous to the ferromagnetic transition in the Ising model, with r playing the role of magnetization and K playing the role of inverse temperature.</Body>

