    <Back>Seizures represent pathological hypersynchronization (r → 1). In Kuramoto terms, this occurs when effective coupling K increases (enhanced excitation, reduced inhibition) or frequency heterogeneity decreases, both lowering the threshold for synchronized states. Anticonvulsants work by raising K_c to prevent this transition.</Back>
  </FlashCard>

