  <H2>Key Equations Summary</H2>

  <Body>For reference, here are the fundamental equations of the Kuramoto model:</Body>

  <Code lang="plaintext">
Kuramoto Model:       dθ_i/dt = ω_i + (K/N) Σ_j sin(θ_j - θ_i)

Order Parameter:      r exp(iψ) = (1/N) Σ_j exp(iθ_j)

Mean-Field Form:      dθ_i/dt = ω_i + Kr sin(ψ - θ_i)

Critical Coupling:    K_c = 2/(πg(0))    [for symmetric unimodal g(ω)]

Lorentzian K_c:       K_c = 2γ           [where g(ω) = (γ/π)/(ω² + γ²)]

Order Parameter
Near Transition:      r ≈ √(1 - K_c/K)   [for K slightly above K_c, Lorentzian]
  </Code>

